  "text": "Occam inversions (Figs. 2b and 5b) were unnecessarily diffuse compared with a difference inversion that otherwise is based on the same type of objective function (i.e., smoothness constraints and a l 2 -norm). This improvement is explained by error cancellation in the difference inversion scheme as outlined by [CITATION_1] .",
